          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Radiological features of COA\n\nReverse figure of '3' sign or double bulge sign or E sign on the left border of aortic shadow is formed by (above downward:- Prestenotic dilatation; coarctation itself (indentation); poststenotic dilatation.\nDouble aortic knuckle.\nDock's sign:- There is bilateral notching of inferior margins of 3-8 ribs. Rib notching is absent in the 1st & 2nd ribs because first and second intercostal arteries do not take part in the collateral circulation. Rib notching increases with age and after the age of 7 years, rib notching is present in almost all the cases."
