          "explanation": "Waters view- \nThe image receptor is placed in front of the patient and perpendicular to the midsagittal plane. The patient’s head is tilted upward so  that  the  canthomeatal  line  forms  a  37-degree  angle  with  the image receptor. If the patient’s mouth is open, the sphenoid sinus is seen superimposed over the palate.\nWhite and Pharoah, Oral radiology, ed 7th, pg-161"
