          "explanation": "Explanation:On ultrasound, the Hydatiform mole resembles a bunch of grapes ('cluster of grapes\" or ''honeycombed uterus\" or \"snow-storm appearance) (See table below) Partial and Complete Hydatiform Mole PARTIAL MOLECOMPLETE MOLEFetus, Fetal vessels, PlacentaPresentAbsentKaryotype69 XXY (triploid)46 XXHydropic changesFocalMarkedMalignant potentialRare1 5-20%Ultrasound featuresFocal cystic spaces in placentaFetus and placenta are seenTransverse diameter of uterus increasesSnowstorm appearance",
