          "explanation": "Ans. a (MCU). (Ref. Sutton Radiology 7th ed. 1017, 1061)- MCU is IOC for PU valve and VUR.Posterior urethral valves (PUV)# Varying degree of chronic urethral obstruction due to fusion and prominence of plicae colliculi, normal concentric folds of urethra.# Usually located in posterior urethra just distal to the level verumontanum.c;# It is the most common cause of severe obstructive uropathy in infants and children.# MCU is 'gold standard' in diagnosis of PUV.# Rx: Cystoscopic fulguration of the valves.Three types of PUV are described :",
