          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "TRETHOWAN'S SIGN In normal hip a line drawn tangential to superior femoral neck (Klein's line) intersects small poion of lateral capital epiphyseal. In posterior displacement of epiphyses the line doesn't intersect.",
          "hint": "Topic: Radiology Q Bank"
