          "explanation": "Ans. B. Anencephalya. The main sonographic feature of anencephaly is symmetric absence of the skull vault, and the cerebral hemispheres but relative preservation of brainstem and portion of midbrain.b. Although on ultrasonographically the diagnosis can be suspected by 12-13 weeks of gestation, it is more reliable by around 15-16 weeks, when the ossification in normal calvarial bones is more obvious.",
