          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Radionuclides react with hydroxyapatite and the pattern of uptake is seen on the bone scan. Strontium-89, Samarium-153, Phosphorus -32, Rhenium-186, Tin -117m emit beta particles with a mean range between 0.2 to 3 mm, minimising toxicity to the surrounding tissues.\nTechnetium 99m emits gamma radiations and is used as a diagnostic tool in medical sciences."
