          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Ultrasound shows a non-communicating dilated tubular structure with a hyperechoic foci within it . Given the clinical scenario, the most probable diagnosis is acute appendicitis with fecolith.",
          "hint": "Topic: Gastrointestinal Radiology"
