          "explanation": "Amongst the given options hemothorax and pneumonia (consolidation) produce opacity on chest X-ray. Pneumonia has nothing to do with blunt chest trauma, while hemothorax is common after blunt chest trauma. Therefore, best answer here is hemothorax.\nPneumothorax causes hypertranslucency (not opacity)."
