          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Deterministic effect: severity increases with dose; practical threshold; the probability of occurrence increases with dose; e.g., cataract.Stochastic effect: severity independent of dose; probability of occurrence increases with dose; no threshold; e.g., cancerReference: Eric J Hall Textbook of Radiobiology for Radiologist; 5th edition",
