          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Ans. D. Bowel obstructionThe CT abdomen shows multiple dilated small intestinal loops, seen in intestinal obstruction. The black shadow anteriorly is of gas in Transverse colon.A bowel larger than 3cm in diameter is associated with small bowel obstructionThe upper limit of normal diameter of the bowel is generally accepted as 3cm for the small bowel, 6cm for the colon and 9cm for the caecum (3/6/9 rule).",
