          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Meningioma can present with headaches, seizures, or focal neurologic deficits. On imaging studies they have a characteristic appearance usually consisting of a paially calcified, densely enhancing extra axial tumor arising from the dura. Occasionally they may have a dural tail, consisting of thickened, enhanced dura extending like a tail from the mass. Ref: DeAngelis L.M., Wen P.Y. (2012). Chapter 379. Primary and Metastatic Tumors of the Nervous System. In D.L. Longo, A.S. Fauci, D.L. Kasper, S.L. Hauser, J.L. Jameson, J. Loscalzo (Eds), Harrison's Principles of Internal Medicine, 18e."
