          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Cleidocranial Dysplasia (Marie and Sainton’s disease, Scheuthauer-Marie-Sainton syndrome, mutational dysostosis)\nAbsence of clavicle causes unusual mobility of the shoulders with the tendency of the patients to bring their shoulders forward till they meet in the midline. Cleidocranial dysplasia is a syndrome of unknown cause. It is usually transmitted as an autosomal dominant trait.\nGorlin sign: It is the ability to touch the tip of the nose with the tongue. It is present in Ehlers-Danlos syndrome."
