          "explanation": "Earliest radiological change of UC on barium enema is blurring of the mucosal lining and a fine granularity when mucosa is seen enface due to edema.\nEarliest radiological change of Crohn's disease → Aphthous lesions (Bull's eye or Target lesions)."
