          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Causes of unilateral elevation of the dome of diaphragm: 1. Idiopathic 2. Eventration 3. Muscular disease 4. Radiation therapy 5. Neurologic disease (Stroke, polio) 6. Trauma, Erb's palsy",
          "hint": "Topic: Gastrointestinal Radiology"
