          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Test for Checking Unsafe Illumination:\nFilm fogging can occur due to:\n\nUse of inappropriate safelight filters.\nExcessive exposure to safelight filters.\nStray light.\nCoin test/Penny test (A and B) is a test to evaluate for fogging caused by inappropriate safe lighting conditions.\n\t\nShut all lights and put on the safelights.\nOpen the unexposed film packet and place the base film in the area where films are usually unwrapped.\nPlace a coin on the film and leave it in this position for approximately the time required to unwrap and mount a full mouth set of radiographs, usually 5 min."
