          "explanation": "Ans. C. Mid diastole* Cardiac CT is done in mid diastole assisted by synchronous ECG gating.* Cardiac CT is an example of multi slice CT/multidetector CT (MDCT).* In spiral CT only one section in one rotation. In MDCT multiple sections in one rotation.* Cardiac CT is done in CAD and for coronary calcium scoring.- Coronary calcium scoring denotes degree of atherosclerosis and is done by the Agatston method.",
