          "explanation": "'Midgut volvulus' is a complication of mal-rotated bowel. It may result in proximal bowel obstruction with resultant ischemia if prompt treatment is not instigated. Radiological Findings on CT include: Whirlpool sign of twisted mesentery Malrotated bowel configuration Inveed SMA/SMV relationship Bowel obstruction Free fluid/free gas in advanced cases",
