          "explanation": "Ans: A (18-FIuorodeoxy...) POSITRON EMISSION TOMOGRAPHY (PET) L & B 25th/ 136-37# PET is an extension of nuclear medicine, in which a positron-emitting substance such as 18F is tagged and used to assess tissue metabolic characteristics.# Nuclear medicine also differs from other means of imaging, which are largely anatomically based, as it also provides functional information.# The most commonly used radiolabelled tracer is 18F-2- fluara-2-deoxy-D-ghicose (FDG), although other tracers can also be used in order to assess metabolic functions such as oxygen and glucose consumption and blood flow.",
